Student Skill Exchange Platform – Refined Plan
Phase 1: Research & Validation
Market Research:

Survey students (universities, colleges) about their needs.

Identify most in-demand skills (programming, tutoring, design, notes).

Competitor Analysis:

Study platforms like Fiverr, Upwork, and Chegg.

Note gaps (student affordability, peer-to-peer trust).

Validation:

Run a small pilot (Google Form or WhatsApp group) to test interest.

Phase 2: Core Design
Platform Model: Decide if it will be a web app, mobile app, or hybrid.

User Roles:

Student (seller/buyer) – can list skills, buy services.

Admin – manages users, disputes, payments.

Key Modules:

Registration & Profiles

Skill Listing & Search

Service Marketplace (notes, tutoring, design)

Payment Integration

Ratings & Reviews

Messaging/Chat

Phase 3: Technical Development
Frontend: React.js / Vue.js (mobile-first design).

Backend: Node.js (Express) or Django.

Database: PostgreSQL or MongoDB.

Authentication: Student email verification, OAuth2.

Payments: Stripe, PayPal, Easypaisa/JazzCash for local support.

Hosting: AWS / Azure / GCP.

Phase 4: Launch Strategy
Pilot Launch:

Start with one university or city.

Offer free credits to early adopters.

Marketing:

Social media campaigns (Instagram, TikTok, LinkedIn).

Campus ambassadors.

Referral bonuses.

Community Building:

Forums, study groups, gamification (skill points, badges).